{
  "doc_id": "4969",
  "text": "Meadow bromegrass (Bromus riparius Rehmann) is a bunch type of bromegrass with good regrowth ability [CITATION_1] . Its leafy production and rapid growth make it desirable for pastures in the central parkland region of Canada [CITATION_2] [2] [CITATION_3] . Due to shorter rhizomes, meadow bromegrass is less aggressive than smooth bromegrass (Bromus inermis Leyss) in perennial grass-legume mixtures [CITATION_4] . Meadow bromegrass is relatively winter-hardy and has shown potential for late summer and fall regrowth [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
